[[File:Que Pasa 2018.png|thumb|120px|Qué Pasa logotype.]] '''''Qué Pasa''''' (meaning ''What's Happening?'' in English) is a lifestyle and [[news magazine]] published in [[Santiago]], [[Chile]].
==History and profile== ''Qué Pasa'' began publication in 1971.<ref>{{cite book|title=The Europa World Year Book 2003|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=XLvU9lroRuUC&pg=PA1066|accessdate=29 October 2015|date=10 July 2003|publisher=Taylor & Francis|isbn=978-1-85743-227-5|page=1066}}</ref> The magazine is owned by [[Copesa]].<ref>{{cite book|author1=David Hugh Weaver|author2=Lars Willnat|title=The Global Journalist in the 21st Century|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=ETE5vVTeLQkC&pg=PA382|accessdate=29 October 2015|year=2012|publisher=Routledge|isbn=978-0-415-88576-8|page=382}}</ref><ref>{{cite book|author1=Lynda Lee Kaid|author2=Christina Holtz-Bacha|title=The SAGE Handbook of Political Advertising|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=ebN1AwAAQBAJ&pg=PA148|accessdate=29 October 2015|date=14 June 2006|publisher=SAGE Publications|isbn=978-1-4522-6154-6|page=148}}</ref> It is published by Empresa Periodística La Tercera, S.A. in [[Spanish language|Spanish]] weekly on Fridays.<ref>{{cite web|title=Que Pasa|url=http://multimediausa.com/assets/magazines/consumer/que-pasa/|publisher=Multimedia, Inc|accessdate=29 October 2015}}</ref><ref name=pub/> The headquarters of the weekly is in Santiago.<ref name=pub>{{cite web|title=Qué Pasa|url=http://www.publicitas.com/latinamerica/media-solutions/factsheet/mediadata/que-pasa-chile/?PARAM1=EZRQS2#.VjHSoGThDC4|work=Publicitas|accessdate=29 October 2015}}</ref> It has a right-wing political stance.<ref>{{cite book|author1=Susan Roraff|author2=Laura Camacho|title=CultureShock! Chile: A Survival Guide to Customs and Etiquette|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=VQ6JAAAAQBAJ&pg=PA129|accessdate=29 October 2015|date=15 February 2011|publisher=Marshall Cavendish International Asia Pte Ltd|isbn=978-981-4435-30-7|page=129}}</ref><ref>{{cite book|author=Leslie Bethell|title=The Cambridge History of Latin America|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=cbhOISlOv3MC&pg=PA813|accessdate=29 October 2015|date=25 October 1991|publisher=Cambridge University Press|isbn=978-0-521-26652-9|page=813}}</ref>
